Subject: Align LEON3 UART IRQ with the Gaisler Nexys A7 reference design

The QEMU upstream LEON3 machine hardcodes the UART interrupt line at IRQ 3.
The Gaisler reference SoC synthesized for the Nexys A7 development board
(used by the OBDH demonstrator and other Termina projects) wires the UART
to IRQ 2 instead. Without this change, RTEMS images built against the
Nexys A7 BSP never see TX/RX interrupts when run under QEMU, breaking any
UART-driven workflow.

The patch is a single-line change to hw/sparc/leon3.c.

Applies cleanly against: qemu-9.2.4

--- a/hw/sparc/leon3.c
+++ b/hw/sparc/leon3.c
@@ -57,7 +57,7 @@
 #define MAX_CPUS  4

 #define LEON3_UART_OFFSET  (0x80000100)
-#define LEON3_UART_IRQ     (3)
+#define LEON3_UART_IRQ     (2)

 #define LEON3_IRQMP_OFFSET (0x80000200)

